    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1AbsoluteLayout" kindref="compound">AbsoluteLayout</ref> positions its children at explicit coordinates. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Children are positioned using attached properties that specify their bounds (x, y, width, height).</para>
<para>Supports:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Absolute positioning with pixel values</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Proportional positioning (0.0 to 1.0 relative to parent)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Proportional sizing (0.0 to 1.0 relative to parent)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<sect1 id="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1AbsoluteLayout_1abs_common_props">
<title>Common Property Behavior</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>RequestedWidth/RequestedHeight</bold>: Only used when the corresponding bounds dimension is negative (auto-size). When bounds width or height is &gt;= 0, the bounds value takes precedence and RequestedWidth/RequestedHeight is ignored.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Alignment:</bold> Not used. Position is determined solely by the bounds x/y values and margin.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Margin:</bold> Applied as an offset to the bounds position. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
    </detaileddescription>
